# Supabase Configuration for ThinkLikeLaw
# 
# IMPORTANT: These are the PUBLIC/ANON keys - they are meant to be exposed in client-side code.
# The security comes from Row Level Security (RLS) policies on your database tables.
# Never use the service_role key in client-side code.
#
# How to set up in Cloudflare Pages:
# 1. Go to your Cloudflare Pages project settings
# 2. Navigate to "Environment Variables" 
# 3. Add these variables:
#   - SUPABASE_URL: https://oxlpmgnytsvdjcibtdmb.supabase.co
#   - SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: sb_publishable_hR5BbCbWqj0V7sZP6lpDjg_sMhNg84A
# 4. Redeploy the site
#
# For local development, copy this file to .env and uncomment the values:
# SUPABASE_URL=https://oxlpmgnytsvdjcibtdmb.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_hR5BbCbWqj0V7sZP6lpDjg_sMhNg84A
